%erg v1
Title: Fix null ribbon: center at Z=0 when null_mean departs from observed mean
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-25
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-25T17:45Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

The ribbon formula in `plot_zoo_results.py::_compute_null_z_threshold`:

    z_threshold = (null_mean ± 1.96 * null_std − mu_w) / sigma_w

places the ribbon at the Z-score that corresponds to the null distribution
mean.  For methods where null_mean ≠ mu_w (mean observed), the ribbon is
offset from Z=0:

| Method          | ribbon center |
|-----------------|--------------|
| C2ST_embedding  | −8.3         |
| C2ST_lexical    | −3.9         |
| S1_MMD          | −1.8         |
| L1, S2–S4       | −0.3 to +0.4 |

For C2ST, the null distribution (chance-level AUC ≈ 0.5) maps to Z ≈ −8
in the crossyear space because the observed mean AUC is ~0.65.  This is
mathematically correct but falls outside the visible plot area and is
uninformative as a significance threshold.

The original intent (ticket 0097) was to replace the flat ±2 box with a
time-varying equivalent — a band showing where "random noise" lands in
Z-score space.  For that purpose the ribbon should be centred at Z=0 with
time-varying half-width 1.96 × null_std / sigma_w.

## Relevant files

- `scripts/plot_zoo_results.py:102` — `_compute_null_z_threshold` —
  formula to change
- `scripts/plot_zoo_results.py:149` — `fill_between` call that uses
  `z_threshold_upper` / `z_threshold_lower`

## Actions

1. Change `_compute_null_z_threshold` to centre the ribbon at Z=0:

   ```python
   hw = 1.96 * null_df["null_std"] / null_df["window"].map(sigma_w)
   null_df["z_threshold_upper"] = +hw
   null_df["z_threshold_lower"] = -hw
   ```

   Drop the `null_mean − mu_w` term.  The ribbon now reads:
   "the null permutation distribution has this ±1.96σ width in
   standardised units, centred at the observed mean."

2. Update the legend label if needed to reflect the new semantics.

3. Rebuild zoo figures and verify C2ST ribbon is visible and near Z=0.

## Test

Red: add a test checking that for a synthetic null_df with large
`null_mean` offset, `_compute_null_z_threshold` returns thresholds
symmetric around 0.

## Verification

- [ ] C2ST_embedding ribbon centre is at Z=0 ± 0.1 (not at −8)
- [ ] G-method ribbons are approximately unchanged (null_mean ≈ mu_w for G)
- [ ] All 18 zoo figures rebuild without error

## Invariants

- For G methods where null_mean ≈ mu_w the ribbon shape should be nearly
  identical to before (since the offset term was near zero anyway).
- Time-varying width (null_std varies by year) must be preserved.

## Exit criteria

- Ribbon visible and near Z=0 for C2ST, S1, and all methods
- PR merged
